main event: A group of college students reported sighting a stationary, blinking object that changed color from white to red to green in the sky over Southampton College in Southampton, New York on November 9, 1966.
interesting points: One observer reported that a red discharge appeared to shoot toward the west and was square-shaped.
Another observer in the same group reported that the object appeared to 'spin in a circle and disappeared suddenly to the north'.
The sighting was believed to be influenced by recent UFO publicity in the local area and reported as a student-group effort.
The object was believed to be a star and the sighting and reports were influenced by group hysteria.
There were no photographs included in the report.
sighted object: A stationary, blinking object that changed color from white to red to green
